                <head>Chamber of Commerce of Dewsbury</head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Dewsbury</placeName>, <date
                        ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-volume-rules" calendar="gregorian"
                        notAfter="1865-07-31T23:59:59+00:00" notBefore="1865-04-15T00:00:00+00:00"
                        >undated</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="italic">Resolution passed by the Chamber of Commerce,
                    Dewsbury</hi>.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Resolved</hi>, That this council expresses its utter
                    abhorrence and detestation of the foul crime which has deprived a kindred nation
                    of its President at such a momentous crisis in its history; and that such
                    expression of the indignation of the council, together with its sympathy, be
                    conveyed to the American consul at Leeds.</p>
                <p>The <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consul</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Leeds</hi>.</p>
            </div>
